28/07/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- Police arrested 38 public officials for economic crimes in the first six months of 2008, according to a semi-annual report presented on Sunday (July 27th). 
According to the document, 419 legal proceedings against current and former officials on suspicion of corruption and money laundering began during the same period. 
The report also notes that illegal drug smuggling to Greece and Italy has declined. 
(Balkanweb, News 24 - 27/07/08; Gazeta Shqiptare - 28/07/08)
